For People hating on the ending. The family's reaction isn't the whole point of the movie, it isn't the pivotal moment you should be waiting for or curious about, the whole movie is about Wakefield's arc, as well as the ending. The family's reaction will only just be a mere consequence of his choice, they could hate him for trying to selfishly find meaning in his own life, or they could embrace him, empathize with him as he's struggling to find meaning in his own life. I believe he would've committed suicide had he not left his "life" in search of his own meaning of life. Would you rather see Wakefield committing suicide early on, and left his family alone forever because he failed to see the joy he would later find in his family and in his life after he had distant himself from his family? Remember, he always had the choice of not returning, but he chose to return to his family. Our fathers' lives don't end as they become fathers, Wakefield's life begins as he ends what he thought was his supposed life.

comments: The gwen-verse

生理的に相容れない者同士が、相互に軋轢を生まないための合理的な区分けは必要だと思う。
日本の東京都には弁護士会が三つあって、弁護士会館をつくるときに第一東京弁護士会だけエレベーターを別につくる要望も根強かったときく。
渉外事務所や企業法務系の仕事が多く高収入の人が多いときく第一東京弁護士会。
蔵書の違いもあるのか、図書館は東京弁護士会と第二東京弁護士会と別個独立に存在する。
目的が不平等な差別か合理的な区別かはよく分からない。ちゃんと調べてないから。
トイレも、男女別、多目的用別があるし、スタッフ用トイレ別のところもある。
この映画ならではの事情を捨象すると何が問題か分かりにくい。
生理的に嫌いならヘルプ不要。
自分で家事育児やればいい。
自分にとって重要な作業を依頼しておいて、自分より不衛生かのように見下すのは背理に思える。
お目当てのコンパニオン指定して飲酒接待させようとしたら、店からヘルプをつけることを押し売りするぼったくりバーも日本にはある。
法律事務所でも、指定の弁護士に依頼したらアソシエイトがいっぱいついてきて弁護士報酬が増えることも。
会社でも、人事権がないと体裁だけ整えたい人事部が最悪な組み合わせで仕事やらせようとしたり。
The という定冠詞の意味は、この映画ではどうだろう。
Helpの仕事のロールモデル提示というよりは、Helpの一般的な地位を強調する感じ？
多くの証言を集めるところは、「ときめきメモリアル」のメモリーカード事件を思い出させる。
制作者の意図を越えて、プレイヤーにパラメータの数値をインチキ設定のメモリーカードを売って稼ぐことに、メーカーの枠を超えて制作者たちが異議を唱えた。
それぞれの思い入れを集めて裁判所に証拠提出。
あの莫大な量をもってしても、フリーライダーの手抜きに違法評価を与えることはハードル高く賠償金もショボすぎた。
バカらしくて二度と生まれたくないと痛感する象徴的事象の一つ。
日本国憲法の象徴一族の一挙手一投足をさらけだしてチヤホヤして見本にしたがる人がシンボルとそのHelpに要求する待遇はものすごい特権。
でも、象徴一族への従属と協調を力ずくで強制される人にとっては、多重の弾圧でしかない。
もはや区分けで済む問題ではない。
こんな醜悪な世に生まれない自由がない。
生んだ者と生き恥さらすことを強要した者たちが責任とるどころか、徹底的に踏みにじって搾取して恥辱を与え、苦しみまみれの延命をさせてまで絞りとろうとするHelp たちは、さらに重い反作用がかえってきて当然だろう。

comments:
I have been doing a little research project this month. I have had extra time as compared to a normal human being who works. And so to kill time, I have been going to a lot of movies. I have been going to an inordinate amount of movies, more movies than an average human being. Naturally, the first thing I did was watch the movies I really wanted to see based on the previews that I had witnessed. I saw Deadpool which I thought was amazing, then I went to see Zootopia, which was the best movie of the year so far. But, then I started watching movies I wouldn't normally go see. I went to see 10 Cloverfield Lane, which was just ok, and then I saw Risen, which I had mistaken for a movie about Roman soldiers. I was right but also very wrong and the movie wasn't that good anyways. I also saw a movie with one of my favorite actors, George Clooney, however that movie ended up being HIS worst. Then I got really bored and went to see movies I didn't even want to see. I went to see The Witch, which was bad, and finally dragged myself into the atrocity of a film The Divergent Series: Allegiant, which made me surprised, because I hadn't killed myself before its credits.

My science experiment was that I made a mental note of the feeling the picture gave me just from the previews. The experiment proved that the preview is a very good indicator on whether a movie is going to be good or bad. I raved about the preview for Deadpool and Zootopia which turned out to be fantastic, and turned my nose up for The Divergent Series: Allegiant which turned out to be a disaster. I had a similar spectrum of feelings for all the movies in the middle. I did not go see The Gods of Egypt. That movie preview was so bad, I decided that I would rather sit in a dark room and listen to grass grow. As it turns out the people who made that film are either fired, broke or both. Maybe they should pick up my hobby.

My point is that The Nice Guys has got my attention. The preview has made me get the inkling that I am really going to enjoy it. Is it the aging Crowe or the young rising Gosling? Maybe it is the setting or the plot, or a combination of the two? I don't know why I am going to enjoy The Nice Guys, but I would be willing to put money down that I will love it. I think that a lot of people will agree with me that WB has got this trailer right, and so the movie must be right as well.

I have never seen so many movies in a short amount of time. I pity you people over in Hollywood. I once thought there was great glamour in the movie business. However the reality of it is that there is a lot of junk to sift through. I am happy that the previews allows us to avoid movies that aren't worth a 2D matinee. I also want to thank the industry for making that fact blatantly obvious.

We will see how my nose fairs for the next month. So far I have smelled a stinky ghost, shook my head at a mothers day movie that smells like an old "friends" sock, and wondered why Tommy Lee Jones is suddenly mute.

Time will tell Youtube... Time will tell...

comments: Ex-Machina is a pure genius of a sci-fi classic. It's like a Stanley Kubrick film meets over Alfred Hitchcock and they combine it into a suspense film. Don't worry, I won't spoil the movie and you know what happens in this twist ending? The film explains about a user who was selected from the Internet and he goes on a field trip to the unknown area where the mountains at. He meets a strange scientist who lives in his secret place and he explains the our main character that the area is the research of artificial intelligence of making robots come to alive. Then, he meets a gorgeous robotic woman who stays inside the room and the scientist wants him to be part of his research to communicate with the robot. He spends time with the robotic girl for few days until the room shuts down and the girl tells the truth that the scientist is a bad person who kept his secret between the robot and him. He tries to convince the scientist, but our main character was stuck in the research facility that he wishes to release the girl that he wants. What will happen that you trust with the robot that she turns just like human can do? Does he trust the robot that he cares or the robot is the one who behind all this? All the answers can figure it out unless you want the our main character to be saved. It's visually stunning that takes place in the strange area that makes you chill while you watch it and our main hero was shock and tense that he is in the strange room that makes it darker and scary. The two actors are great including our main hero is questionable and skeptical about the area and the scientist is unlikable, but he keeps it secret that he's a humble guy that you don't mess around with him. Eva was great and one of the best robotic characters ever with beautifully design of herself and the actress was great to become a robot who spends her whole time that she wants to be him or out. The direction is great with wonderful script, nicely cinematography, and great sci-fi idea to make it classic. It's a must see film that you prefer this movie a classic sci-fi film of the 2015. Great story, great acting, great actors, and wonderful shots. Ex-Machina is a pure genius film that the robot can relate.

Talk about a movie that looked and acted smarter than it actually was. The acting, the ideas, the tone.. they have all been done before, but better. Cerebral film making takes more than ambient music and pretty backdrops. This definitely does not work as a psychological thriller.

I'd suggest checking out Under the Skin. it's not without its problems, but it actually works a a movie that hits you deep and you'll be glad you didn't miss it.
